import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node sizes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.barplot(x="size", y="name", data=data, estimator=lambda x: sum(x) / len(x))
    plt.axvline(x=data['size'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean size')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Average size')
    plt.ylabel('Node name')
    plt.title('What is the average size of nodes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='parent', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['parent'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['parent'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of parent nodes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between node size and parent node?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['size'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median size')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='name', data=data, order=data['name'].value_counts().index, palette='viridis')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Node Name')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the most common node name in the tree?')
    plt.axhline(y=data['name'].value_counts().max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['name'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
